_meta.title: Complete Catalog of Mathematical Symbols & Notation
sources: Combining Diacritical Marks for Symbols U+20D0-20FF

01_greek_lowercase.description: Greek lowercase letters used in mathematics

symbols.name: alpha
symbols.usage: Angles, significance level (statistics), fine-structure constant, angular acceleration

symbols.name: beta
symbols.usage: Beta function, regression coefficient, inverse temperature (1/kT), second angle

symbols.name: gamma
symbols.usage: Euler-Mascheroni constant, Lorentz factor, gamma function argument, third angle

symbols.name: delta
symbols.usage: Dirac delta function, Kronecker delta, infinitesimal change, variation

symbols.name: epsilon
symbols.usage: Arbitrarily small positive quantity, permittivity, Levi-Civita symbol

symbols.name: lunate epsilon
symbols.usage: Variant epsilon used in set membership notation, analysis

symbols.name: eta
symbols.usage: Dirichlet eta function, metric tensor component, learning rate, efficiency

symbols.name: theta
symbols.usage: Angle (especially polar/spherical), Jacobi theta function, Heaviside step function

symbols.name: theta symbol (script theta)
symbols.usage: Variant theta in thermodynamics, curly theta for special functions

symbols.name: iota
symbols.usage: Inclusion map, index, imaginary unit (some notations)

symbols.name: kappa
symbols.usage: Curvature, condition number, connectivity, spring constant

symbols.name: kappa symbol (variant kappa)
symbols.usage: Variant kappa in some technical contexts

symbols.name: lambda
symbols.usage: Eigenvalue, wavelength, Lagrange multiplier, lambda calculus, decay constant

symbols.name: mu
symbols.usage: Mean (statistics), measure (measure theory), micro- prefix, Mobius function, magnetic permeability

symbols.name: nu
symbols.usage: Frequency, degrees of freedom, kinematic viscosity, neutrino

symbols.name: xi
symbols.usage: Random variable, dummy variable of integration, coherence length

symbols.name: omicron
symbols.usage: Big O notation variant (rare, usually Latin O), order of magnitude

symbols.name: pi
symbols.usage: Circle constant 3.14159..., prime-counting function, projection, product operator

symbols.name: pi symbol (variant pi / pomega)
symbols.usage: Variant pi, used in some older notation

symbols.name: rho
symbols.usage: Density, resistivity, correlation coefficient, spectral radius, charge density

symbols.name: rho symbol (variant rho)
symbols.usage: Curly rho variant, used in some physics/analysis contexts

symbols.name: final sigma
symbols.usage: Rarely used mathematically (word-final form in Greek)

symbols.name: sigma
symbols.usage: Standard deviation, sigma-algebra, stress tensor, surface charge density, Pauli matrices

symbols.name: tau
symbols.usage: Torque, proper time, time constant, tau function (Ramanujan), torsion, 2*pi

symbols.name: phi
symbols.usage: Euler totient function, angle (azimuthal), electric potential, phase angle, basis functions

symbols.name: phi symbol (straight phi)
symbols.usage: Variant phi, often used for the golden ratio 1.618..., scalar field

symbols.name: chi
symbols.usage: Chi-squared distribution, characteristic function, susceptibility, Euler characteristic

symbols.name: psi
symbols.usage: Wave function (quantum mechanics), digamma function, supergolden ratio, stream function

symbols.name: omega
symbols.usage: Angular velocity/frequency, first transfinite ordinal, cube root of unity, differential form

02_greek_uppercase.description: Greek uppercase letters used in mathematics

symbols.name: Gamma
symbols.usage: Gamma function, Christoffel symbols, graph (graph theory), circulation

symbols.name: Delta
symbols.usage: Finite difference/change, discriminant, Laplace operator, symmetric difference

symbols.name: Theta
symbols.usage: Big Theta notation (complexity), angular displacement, Heaviside function

symbols.name: Lambda
symbols.usage: Diagonal matrix of eigenvalues, lattice, cosmological constant, Lebesgue measure, von Mangoldt function

symbols.name: Xi
symbols.usage: Grand canonical partition function, cascade hyperon, Riemann Xi function

symbols.name: Sigma
symbols.usage: Summation operator, covariance matrix, surface, sigma-algebra

symbols.name: Phi
symbols.usage: Cumulative distribution function (normal), magnetic flux, golden ratio (uppercase form)

symbols.name: Omega
symbols.usage: Ohm (resistance), sample space, solid angle, asymptotic lower bound, Chaitin's constant, last ordinal

03_greek_archaic_and_special.description: Archaic/special Greek letters used in mathematics

symbols.name: Digamma (uppercase)
symbols.usage: Digamma function (rare), number 6 in Greek numeral system

symbols.name: nabla (inverted delta)
symbols.usage: Gradient, divergence, curl (del operator) -- originally Greek but now a math operator

04_hebrew_letters.description: Hebrew letters used in mathematics (transfinite cardinals, set theory)

symbols.name: alef symbol
symbols.usage: Aleph numbers: cardinality of infinite sets (aleph-0 = countable infinity, aleph-1, etc.)

symbols.name: bet symbol
symbols.usage: Beth numbers: cardinality in set theory (beth-0 = aleph-0, beth-1 = |R|)

symbols.name: gimel symbol
symbols.usage: Gimel function in set theory: gimel(kappa) = kappa^cf(kappa)

symbols.name: dalet symbol
symbols.usage: Daleth number (rare), used in cardinal arithmetic

symbols.name: alef (Hebrew)
symbols.usage: Alternate form of aleph for transfinite numbers

symbols.name: ayin (Hebrew)
symbols.usage: Extremely rare: used in Morse & Feschbach for tensor equations

symbols.name: yod (Hebrew)
symbols.usage: Extremely rare: used in Morse & Feschbach for tensor equations

05_blackboard_bold.description: Blackboard bold (double-struck) letters -- number sets and algebraic structures

symbols.name: double-struck capital P
symbols.usage: Projective space, probability measure, prime numbers

symbols.name: double-struck capital A
symbols.usage: Affine space, algebraic numbers, ring of adeles

symbols.name: double-struck capital D
symbols.usage: Unit disk in complex plane, decimal fractions

symbols.name: double-struck capital I
symbols.usage: Identity matrix, imaginary numbers, indicator function

symbols.name: double-struck small pi
symbols.usage: Mathematical constant pi in double-struck form

symbols.name: double-struck digit one
symbols.usage: Identity element, indicator function, top element in forcing

06_script_calligraphic.description: Script/calligraphic letters used in mathematics (Letterlike Symbols + Math Alphanumeric Symbols)

symbols.name: fraktur capital G
symbols.usage: Lie algebra of a Lie group G

symbols.name: fraktur capital H
symbols.usage: Lie algebra of a Lie group H, Cartan subalgebra

symbols.name: fraktur small g
symbols.usage: Lie algebra of Lie group G

symbols.name: fraktur small o
symbols.usage: Ring of integers in number field

symbols.name: colon equals
symbols.usage: Definition (x := y means x is defined as y)

symbols.name: subset of
symbols.usage: Proper subset (or subset in some conventions)

symbols.name: square image of or equal to
square original of or equal to
circled dot operator
symbols.usage: Direct product, Hadamard product, inner product

symbols.name: normal subgroup of or equal to
element of
symbols.usage: x in A: x is member of set A

symbols.name: contains as member
symbols.usage: A contains x (reverse of element of)

symbols.name: subset of
symbols.usage: A is proper subset of B

symbols.name: superset of
symbols.usage: A is proper superset of B

symbols.name: subset of or equal to
symbols.usage: A is subset of or equal to B

symbols.name: superset of or equal to
symbols.usage: A is superset of or equal to B

symbols.name: not a subset of
symbols.usage: A is not subset of B

symbols.name: not a superset of
symbols.usage: A is not superset of B

symbols.name: intersection
symbols.usage: A intersect B: elements in both

symbols.name: union
symbols.usage: A union B: elements in either

symbols.name: set minus
symbols.usage: A minus B: elements in A not in B

symbols.name: there exists
symbols.usage: Existential quantifier: there exists an x

symbols.name: there does not exist
symbols.usage: Negated existential: no x exists such that

11_arrows.description: Arrow symbols used in mathematics (U+2190-21FF selected)

symbols.name: rightwards arrow
symbols.usage: Function mapping (f: A -> B), tends to, implies

symbols.name: left right double arrow
symbols.usage: If and only if (iff), logical equivalence

12_latin_special.description: Latin letters with special mathematical meanings

symbols.name: small a
symbols.usage: Coefficient, constant, first term of sequence, semi-major axis

symbols.name: small b
symbols.usage: Coefficient, constant, second term, semi-minor axis

symbols.name: small c
symbols.usage: Speed of light, constant of integration, cardinality of continuum

symbols.name: small e
symbols.usage: Euler's number 2.71828..., basis of natural logarithm, eccentricity

symbols.name: small g
symbols.usage: Function, gravitational acceleration, metric tensor, genus

symbols.name: small i
symbols.usage: Imaginary unit (sqrt(-1)), index variable, unit vector

symbols.name: small j
symbols.usage: Imaginary unit (engineering), index variable, unit vector

symbols.name: small k
symbols.usage: Index variable, Boltzmann constant, curvature, unit vector

symbols.name: small l
symbols.usage: Length, angular momentum quantum number, line

symbols.name: small n
symbols.usage: Integer variable, dimension, sample size, normal vector

symbols.name: small q
symbols.usage: Charge, generalized coordinate, probability (complement), prime power

symbols.name: small s
symbols.usage: Arc length, Laplace variable, standard deviation (sample)

symbols.name: small u
symbols.usage: Variable, unit step function, substitution variable

symbols.name: small z
symbols.usage: Third variable, complex variable, z-score, height

symbols.name: capital E
symbols.usage: Expected value, energy, set, electric field

symbols.name: capital G
symbols.usage: Group, gravitational constant, graph, Green's function

symbols.name: capital H
symbols.usage: Hamiltonian, Hilbert space, entropy, hypothesis, Hessian

symbols.name: capital I
symbols.usage: Identity matrix, integral, current, moment of inertia

symbols.name: capital N
symbols.usage: Natural numbers, normal distribution, cardinality, neutrons

symbols.name: capital P
symbols.usage: Probability, permutation P(n,k), point, polynomial, projection

symbols.name: capital Q
symbols.usage: Rational numbers, charge, quotient, quadratic form

symbols.name: capital R
symbols.usage: Real numbers, radius, resistance, curvature radius, ring

symbols.name: capital S
symbols.usage: Set, surface, sum, action (physics), symmetric group

symbols.name: capital U
symbols.usage: Universal set, unitary group/matrix, potential energy, open set

symbols.name: capital Z
symbols.usage: Integers, partition function, atomic number, impedance

13_basic_arithmetic.description: Basic arithmetic and common mathematical symbols

symbols.name: plus-minus sign
symbols.usage: Plus or minus, uncertainty, error bound

symbols.name: minus-or-plus sign
symbols.usage: Minus or plus (opposite sign of pm)

symbols.name: vertical line
symbols.usage: Absolute value, divisibility, conditional probability, norm

14_miscellaneous_math_symbols.description: Miscellaneous Mathematical Symbols-A (U+27C0-27EF) and B (U+2980-29FF) -- selected

symbols.name: math left double angle bracket
symbols.usage: Double angle bracket, formal power series

15_combining_diacritical_marks.description: Combining diacritical marks used as mathematical accents (U+0300-036F and U+20D0-20FF)

symbols.name: combining grave accent
symbols.usage: Accent in some notations (contravariant index marker)

symbols.name: combining circumflex (hat)
symbols.usage: Unit vector (x-hat), estimator in statistics, Fourier transform

symbols.name: combining tilde
symbols.usage: Approximation, equivalence relation, dual space, complement

symbols.name: combining breve
symbols.usage: Short vowel (rare in math), sometimes time derivative

symbols.name: combining low line (underline)
symbols.usage: Underlining for emphasis or different variable

symbols.name: combining long solidus overlay
symbols.usage: Negation stroke through symbol (not equal, etc.)

symbols.name: double-struck C
symbols.usage: Complex numbers (also in blackboard bold section)

symbols.name: ohm sign
symbols.usage: Ohms (electrical resistance), also used as Omega

symbols.name: line integration not including the pole
integral with leftwards arrow with hook

18_geometric_shapes.description: Geometric shapes used as mathematical symbols

symbols.name: white square
symbols.usage: Necessity (modal logic), end of proof variant

19_number_forms_and_constants.description: Mathematical constants and special number representations

symbols.name: double-struck italic small e
symbols.usage: Euler's number e in special typography

20_subscript_superscript.description: Superscript and subscript forms used in mathematical notation

21_brackets_delimiters.description: Brackets and delimiters used in mathematical notation

symbols.name: left parenthesis
symbols.usage: Grouping, function arguments, open interval, tuple

symbols.name: right parenthesis
symbols.usage: Grouping, function arguments, open interval, tuple

symbols.name: left square bracket
symbols.usage: Closed interval, matrix, floor function, Iverson bracket
